<h2>Choice Words</h2>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Release Date:</strong> December 2016</li>
  <li><strong>Credits:</strong> Director and Writer</li>
  <li><strong>Runtime:</strong> 7 minutes 18 seconds</li>
  <li>
    <strong>Synopsis:</strong> Without speaking a word, &quot;Choice Words&quot;
    stands as a metaphorical narrative exploring the sometimes difficult choices
    we all have to make throughout our lives.
    Thoughtful cinematic techniques are employed to express a simple but
    meaningful narrative that explores the conflict between personal desires and
    societal expectations.
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>Production Notes:</strong> Benjamin Patch and his producing
    partner/wife, Leslie Patch recruited, organized, and lead a cast and crew of
    20 talented students and alumni of Binghamton University to produce this
    film.
    Of interesting note, the endless tunnel is a cinematic illusion.
    Instead of forking off endlessly in both directions,
    the shooting location has a wall behind the camera.
    Careful camera placement, editing, seamless CGI, and a mirrored image come
    together to create a space in the viewer's mind that in reality,
    does not exist.
  </li>
</ul>

