<h2>Iceland Montage</h2>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Release Date:</strong> July 2016</li>
  <li><strong>Credits:</strong> Cinematographer and Editor</li>
  <li><strong>Runtime:</strong> 5 minutes 35 seconds</li>
  <li>
    <strong>Synopsis:</strong> A montage of carefully composed shots from
    various locations around Iceland. This film is entirely nonverbal &ndash;
    the breathtaking landscapes and rhythmic editing to music speak best for
    themselves.
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>Production Notes:</strong> Much effort was taken to maximize the
    dynamic range of the Sony FS-100 camera that was used.
    Note how details from bright clouds as well as dark shadows are retained.
    Each shot was recorded using a narrow color profile (log-like)
    that was expanded in post-production to maximize the color reproduction
    from this 8-bit camera.
    The music is a series of pre-recorded loops precisely arranged to complement
    the visuals.
  </li>
</ul>

